# Data Model — DeFi

## Entities

### Entity: Vault

ERC-4626 compliant yield vault.

```yaml
entity: Vault
type: contract
properties:
  name:
    type: string
    required: true
  symbol:
    type: string
    required: true
  underlying:
    type: string
    required: true
  totalAssets:
    type: number
    required: true
  performanceFee:
    type: number
    required: false
states: [initialized, active, paused, emergency]
lifecycle: initialized → active → paused → emergency
```

### Entity: Strategy

Yield-generating strategy.

```yaml
entity: Strategy
type: contract
properties:
  name:
    type: string
    required: true
  vault:
    type: string
    required: true
  apy:
    type: number
    required: true
  tvl:
    type: number
    required: true
  risk:
    type: enum
    required: true
states: [proposed, active, harvesting, closed]
lifecycle: proposed → active → harvesting → closed
```

### Entity: Share

ERC-20 token representing vault ownership.

```yaml
entity: Share
type: contract
properties:
  vault:
    type: string
    required: true
  totalSupply:
    type: number
    required: true
  pricePerShare:
    type: number
    required: true
states: [active]
lifecycle: active → active
```

### Entity: Yield

Accrued returns from strategies.

```yaml
entity: Yield
type: event
properties:
  amount:
    type: number
    required: true
  strategy:
    type: string
    required: true
  timestamp:
    type: number
    required: true
states: [harvested, distributed]
lifecycle: harvested → distributed
```

## Relationships

### Relationship: Vault → Strategy

```yaml
relationship: Vault -> Strategy
verb: deploys
cardinality: 1:N
required: true
description: Vault deploys capital into strategies
```

### Relationship: Strategy → Yield

```yaml
relationship: Strategy -> Yield
verb: produces
cardinality: 1:N
required: true
description: Strategy harvests yield
```

### Relationship: Vault → Share

```yaml
relationship: Vault -> Share
verb: mints
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
description: Vault mints shares on deposit
```
